benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId} - Transfer a bundle to another account

covered: Valid Payload: Multiple scenarios cover successful transfers with minimum required fields (TC01) and with all optional parameters (TC02).
Invalid Payload: Several scenarios test invalid bundleId format (TC08), invalid requestedDate (TC09), invalid billingPolicy (TC10), missing required header (TC11), and missing required body (TC12).
Authorization: Tests include missing header (TC11) and unauthorized access (TC13).
Server Error Handling: Scenarios for service unavailable (TC14) and internal server error due to dependency data (TC24) are present.
Large Payloads: Tests address large pluginProperty payloads (TC20).
Validation: SQL injection (TC15) and XSS attempts (TC16) are tested, along with various input validations.

Duplicate Submission/Edge Case Coverage: Various edge cases are covered (TC18 empty pluginProperty array, TC19 extra parameters, TC25 transfer to same account, TC26 backward compatibility, TC31 accessibility).
Performance: Tests for response time under normal load (TC27), peak load (TC28), and concurrency (TC29) are included.
Security/Access Control: Tests include authorization headers, missing headers, and invalid tokens (TC13, TC11).
gaps: Caching Behavior: There are no tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or related caching behavior for POST responses.

Pagination: Not applicable for a single resource transfer scenario, but guideline mentions pagination for large datasets; no explicit pagination tests are present (though not strictly required for POST).
Duplicate Submission: No explicit test case focusing on idempotency or handling of duplicate submissions is present.
Retry/Resilience Semantics: Apart from TC17 recovery from transient network failure, there could be more explicit resilience tests (e.g., repeated retries under varying failure modes).
recommendations: Add tests for caching headers and caching behavior on POST responses (ETag/Cache-Control).
Include an explicit idempotent/duplicate submission test to verify behavior when the same transfer request is made twice.
Add explicit pagination-related tests only if the API surface or responses can paginate in related endpoints; otherwise document as not applicable for this POST.
Consider more resilience/retry scenarios beyond the one recovery test (TC17) to strengthen retry semantics under different transient failures.
